  "prompt": "How much does it cost to ship a kitten?",
  "response": "The cost to ship a kitten can vary significantly based on several factors including:\n\n1. **Shipping Method**: Air freight is the most common method, and costs can range from $100 to $500 or more, depending on the airline, distance, and whether the kitten is shipped alone or with other pets.\n\n2. **Veterinary Expenses**: You may need to cover a health certificate from a veterinarian, which can cost around $50-$150.\n\n3. **Carrier and Supplies**: A pet carrier, bedding, food, and water supplies may add another $30-$100.\n\n4. **Destination**: Shipping costs can vary based on whether you're sending the kitten domestically or internationally.\n\n5. **Shipping Company**: Different companies may have varying rates and service levels.\n\nOverall, you might expect to pay anywhere from $200 to over $1,000 when all expenses are considered. Always check specific regulations and requirements for pet shipping in your area and for your destination.",
